{
  "texts": [
    "Then, we remove prompts for which the three most agreeing prompts have too large a disagreement (e.g.",
    "one finds the response to be perfectly helpful while another finds it to be slightly helpful).",
    "Such a large degree of disagreement typically suggests that one or more of the annotators overlooked or misunderstood an important aspect of the response.",
    "Edit Demonstration seeks to show how humans edit responses by training the model to generate an edited response given a user prompt, a model response and a set of feedback.",
    "We first filter out any feedback that starts with that 'The model response is perfectly helpful' because such type of feedback does not contain any suggestion for improvement."
  ]
}